metadata.name: Possible Ways #4
metadata.description:
This project is written in javascript without using any other libraries, and it is an endless real-time software animation.

The appearance of each token is initially determined by the hash, but the size and positions of its elements change randomly over time, creating an infinite performance.

While working on this project, I was inspired by the elusiveness of the moment, that cannot be saved or predicted. It can only be experienced.

metadata.name: Learning to Fly #95
metadata.description:
This artwork renders a paper canvas-like texture and creates curves mimicking strokes of an ink pen.

It's coded entirely in p5.js and is best viewed on a screen bigger than a mobile phone, while listening to this track called ‘Learning to Fly' by Pink Floyd: 
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nVhNCTH8pDs

Artwork loads at 1000px by 1000px resolution by default. Press ‘2’,’4’ or ‘8’ to load as 2000px by 2000px, 4000px by 4000px or 8000px by 8000px respectively.

Press 's' at any time to download the rendered resolution.

metadata.name: Diyalebuka #129
metadata.description:
Diyalebuka - "Thank you"! 

With this piece I hope to express my thanks and joy for being alive and able to create art. I hope the patterns and textures will bring you joy.

This piece is inspired by the patterns of the Ndebele of Southern Africa and the First Nations Salish of Vancouver Island.

* There are over 100 palettes arranged into 6 distinct families
* There can be between 2 and 10 bars

(The artwork will fit your available window and may take a while to generate if it's a larger resolution)

metadata.name: Indistinct Places #70
metadata.description:
There's a certain state you fall into when you're half asleep that feels very warm and nostalgic. Most of the time, you imagine places or situations that are a mixture of the familiar and the unfamiliar, a strange brew of your past and the future you desire.
"Indistinct Places" is a tribute to this fuzzy state.

/////

Takes a long time to render.
In case you get bored: click on the canvas to start the algorithmic audio.

key "1" - "6": increases the render resolution by 2x with each step
-> These will automatically export a png after the simulation is done.
(Alternatively, you can contact me on Twitter and i can render a high res file in the size you need).

key "s": saves a png with the current resolution

Tone.js is used for the audio.

metadata.name: Release #24
metadata.description:
[…]

More than anything she had wanted to show him where she had lived, where, at a specific time every year, endless fields sent a new cycle of pods on their way.

She preferred to experience these moments alone, imagining the spectacle was being performed just for her. The whole act carried a promise of new beginnings, of paths yet to be taken.

She wasn't really part of any of this, but she too had the coordinates to her own life programmed into her genes.

Any decision would be true now, any path free.

A chorus of explosions sounded as the field burst open.

[…]

–

You can append these parameters to the URL:

[scale=<number>] scale the renderer.
[long-side=<number>] define the number of pixels of the longest side.
[animation=false] skip animating the lines.
[mode=monotone] activate monotone mode.
[detail=<number 0–1>] coarser (0) or finer (1) lines, default: 0.5.

Press [control / command + s] or [tap and hold] to save the current frame.
	- in normal mode: PNG file.
	- in monotone mode: SVG file, suitable for plotting.

Note: The monotone SVG file has no defined dimensions. It is suitable for plotting at 30 × 30 cm. with a 0.25 mm. pen tip. When plotting in larger sizes, you can increase the [detail] parameter to keep contrast with the same pen.

© 2022 Monokai.

metadata.name: Primordial #181
metadata.description:
Primordial is a study of abstract forms. The algorithm, written in p5.js and WebGL, utilizes domain warping to create twisted fields of color and then overlays thousands of tiny lines to provide depth and texture. The outputs are chaotic but not completely formless, like a swirling mass of plasma from the early universe, or a strange proto-life form suspended in prehistoric ooze.

CONTROLS:

1-9: Increase resolution and save image in PNG format

B: Toggle borders on/off

F: Fullscreen
P: Portrait
L: Landscape
S: Square

For third party license information, please see license.md

David Brice Allen
October 2022

metadata.name: Tumble Down Light Factory #134
metadata.description:
Tumble Down Light Factory is an interpretation of light installations & murals.

It attempts to trigger the feeling of coming up on a new block in a new city to discover an unexpected piece of art that is stories tall or entering a new room, knowing there will be a projection dominating the space with its light and color.

This is an abstract distillation of those things and those feelings.

Each composition is initially drawn to a hidden “template” canvas which is sampled and then rendered on the main canvas in various ways after applying some transforms to give it some depth (and so you can actually see it.)

Viewing in full-screen is nice. You should try it.

T : Save hidden ‘template’ image
S : Save current resolution
1 -> 5 : Save low -> high resolution

metadata.name: Absorbed #395
metadata.description:
A collaboration between leading British high-end audio brand KEF, generative artist hieroglyphica, and creative studio Parameta, Absorbed embodies the process of noise becoming high-fidelity sound through KEF’s Metamaterial Absorption Technology (MAT™). 

MAT™ makes the KEF sound what it is: absorbing unwanted distortion to deliver pure, accurate sound exactly as the artist intended. Inspired by this intricacy, Absorbed illustrates pseudorandom networks of patterns, slowly emerging and transforming into the maze-like form of MAT™. Clarity is revealed, noise is absorbed – high-fidelity is found.

The noise fields used in Absorbed are of two distinct types: conventional gradient noise and “sinusoidal” noise, an original algorithm developed for this series. The use of animation as artistic medium reflects the artists’ belief that no single frame can capture the full range of complexity found in the tension between sound and noise, and lets collectors observe for themselves this ever-shifting dialogue. A more extensive discussion of the algorithms used in Absorbed can be found in hieroglyphica’s companion article on fx(text).

- spacebar will pause and resume the animation
- s will save a still image of the current frame
- technically minded collectors can consult the index.html file for info on how to render and save high-resolution images
- use of hardware acceleration in Chrome may impact performance

Founded by BBC engineer Raymond Cooke in 1961, KEF is a leading British innovator of high-end audio products including HiFi speakers, subwoofers, architectural speakers, wireless speaker-systems, and headphones. Find out more at kef.com or visit our Discord at discord.com/invite/u48Z9yjY2q.

metadata.name: Joy Division #325
metadata.description:
As New Dawn Fades it was time to release this project. It's about division and why not reference this band I listened when I was young...
There are different filling possibilities, explore the infinite variations...

Made with p5js, chroma-js and scribble.

Paris. February 2022.
tags: Generative art. Joy Division. Tidally Disrupted Star.

metadata.name: fx(Unit of truth) #5
metadata.description:
I'm trying to reproduce my hallucinations, which I believe stem from some of the mis-signals or over-signals in the process of deconstructing reality in consciousness. Just as we adjust the system through mistakes, these misinformation also contain clues of "essence"

This is an experiment. In my continuous creation of related works in the [Unit of truth] series, I mostly construct the things I want to express subjectively, but this time, I want you to participate in the expression, so I designed this work [fx(Unit of truth)] to let me See what you want to express
